{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9fc45c71-e1c7-4b76-a3e2-4cbba95cbc1a","content":"No files found in the current directory. Since you described the page conceptually, here's exactly how to convert it:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\nIn `SettingsPage.xaml`, add the `x:DataType` directive on the `ContentPage` root element (adjust the `xmlns:vm` namespace to match your project):\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is **`x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`** — this tells the XAML compiler the type of the `BindingContext`, so every `{Binding}` on this page is validated and compiled.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nEnable **strict mode** in your `.csproj` so typos/type-mismatches become *build errors* instead of silent runtime failures:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat invalid compiled bindings as errors -->\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith this, if you wrote `{Binding Themee}` (typo) or bound `FontSize` to a `string`-only property, **`dotnet build` will fail** with a clear error pointing to the offending line.\n\n### 3. Important caveats\n\n- **Opting out locally**: If a subtree binds to a different/unknown type (e.g., a `DataTemplate`), set `x:DataType=\"\"` on that element to revert to reflection-based binding.\n- **`x:DataType` is inherited**: child elements inherit the declared type, so you only need it once at the root unless the context changes.\n- The code-behind (`BindingContext = new SettingsViewModel();`) stays the same — `x:DataType` only informs the compiler; it doesn't set the context.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"79b50fd6-daee-4082-8cac-3dbcfbfa0950","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No files found. The user is asking about a page they have but it's not in the current directory. Let me check what's in the current directory.","outputTokens":785,"requestId":"100C:2D5697:14E4AEC:177A6C0:69FD33C1"},"id":"2f4f2460-8144-4697-9336-af7a40de25fb","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:52:32.649Z","parentId":"5f6f81c6-d321-485c-a421-11b2470c32bb"}
